   <documentation>
      <row>
         <Docu><![CDATA[Creates a backup of all data before the given date. For each table in the datastore a file with _[table name].copy based on the provided base path and file name will be created.
E.g: Date before: 2016-01-01 00:00:00.0+00 and path + base file name: C:\backup\analytcs_2016_01_01_00_00_00 will create the following files: 
C:\backup\analytcs_2016_01_01_00_00_00_ah.copy, 
C:\backup\analytcs_2016_01_01_00_00_00_ah_enricher.copy, 
C:\backup\analytcs_2016_01_01_00_00_00_ara_execution.copy, 
C:\backup\analytcs_2016_01_01_00_00_00_ara_execution_enricher.copy, 
DATASTORE_BACKUP_AND_REMOVE  template is using this action and just creates the base file name based on the given date.

The actions outputs the create base file path &ANALYTICS_BACKUP_BASE_FILENAME# as well as the number of copied records for each table (&ANALYTICS_AH_COUNT#,&ANALYTICS_ARA_COUNT#).

You can use the &ANALYTICS_BACKUP_BASE_FILENAME# to compress the created backup or to move it to another server with a simple wildcard search like : "&ANALYTICS_BACKUP_BASE_FILENAME#*.copy"
]]></Docu>
      </row>
   </documentation>
   <scripts>
      <row>
         <process><![CDATA[:SET &gen_filename# = STR_SUB(&ANALYTICS_BEFORE_DATE#,"-","_")
:SET &gen_filename# = STR_SUB(&gen_filename#," ","_")
:SET &gen_filename# = STR_SUB(&gen_filename#,":","_")
:SET &UC4RB_CONVERTED_STRING# = &ANALYTICS_BACKUP_TARGET#
:INC PCK.ITPA_SHARED.PRV.INCLUDE.ADD_TRAILING_SLASH
:SET &ANALYTICS_BACKUP_BASE_FILENAME# = &UC4RB_CONVERTED_STRING#
:SET &ANALYTICS_BACKUP_BASE_FILENAME# = "&ANALYTICS_BACKUP_BASE_FILENAME#analytics_backup_&gen_filename#"
!make sure utc is set
:PSET &date_before_with_tz# = '&ANALYTICS_BEFORE_DATE#.0+00']]></process>
      </row>
   </scripts>
